==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Apterous
<hw>Ap"ter*ous</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Destitute of wings; apteral; <as>as,
<ex>apterous</ex> insects</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Destitute of winglike membranous
expansions, as a stem or petiole; -- opposed to
<contr>alate</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Apteryges</ent>⟦br⟧
